{
  "stem": "9156.9",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They said they were used to sleep four people in one room.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We had to talk about accepting various cultures.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But I also, in Israel, had very good Arab friends.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I want to say a few more things on that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This is a drawing by Fritz-- F-R-I-T-Z-- Lederer-- L-E, D, as in Dorsey, E-R-E-R-- done 1946 in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it is called And what Fritz Lederer shows there is the Magen Dovid, almost in a suffering head of Christ.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But at the same time, in the lower part, to the left, is the concentration camp where it was.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I think it was Treblinka.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And to the right is the hope that are the ships with the Magen Dovid that lead into freedom.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now, he was, for many-- for quite awhile, I don't know how long, in that concentration camp-- I have a whole map, drawings from that concentration camp-- and was then liberated in 1945.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was sick, got into a hospital.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And because the people in his hometown were afraid what he would tell about them, they killed him.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They snuck into the hospital and killed him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I got this, the whole map, from an extraordinary woman-- her name is Mary N.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Berle-- B-E-R-L-E-- whom I had in one of my courses when I returned to Germany and who was a half, quote, 'half-Jew,' quote, and has lived, also, through terrible times.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And this was her special friend.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And she gave me the whole map, so that I should have it.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
